@node Introduction

                           Introduction

    Why did I put these disks together? Well it all started when a friend
of mine bought an Amiga 1200 and like most people did not have a clue how
to use the Workbench never mind the AmigaDOS. He told me he bought
'Basically Amiga' but he had trouble getting starting with it, so I looked 
at the disks and he was right.  It gave some good info but sometimes it 
would crash the system.  Well he kept ringing up with another question, so 
in the end I decided to put these disks together. He later said, and I quote:

"They are great I think the idea of double - clicking on Icons and
 opening Windows and using your Workbench menu program, are fab. You have
 really thought about the beginner."

        The idea of these two disks is to Introduce you to the Workbench 2
 or 3, I thought the best way to get to no your way around the Workbench is 
to actually click on icons, open drawers and use the menus but instead of
starting programs you get a READ ME file on that subject. After all getting 
to know anything is to experiment.

        This Workbench is a reconstruction of Workbench 2.0, and Workbench
3.0 extra programs added, the program's themselve's have been taken off but
their icons have been left on. I have changed the icons to project-icons to
call AmigaGuide files. So the idea is you open windows double-click on
their icons and they call the AmigaGuide files on that subject.

        I've done it this way so you will get to know your way around the
Workbench and Extras disks.

        I have also put together a program called Workbench Menu's, the 
idea is that it is a reconstruction of the Workbench Menu's, the program 
will be at the top of the screen, when you click on 'Now I know 
(close Window and load Workbench)' then follow the instructions in the Menus
Window.

        When looking at any of the pictures, just click the left mouse
button, to continue. If your looking at an Animation then click your right
mouse button to continue. All the Picture's and Animation's are on the
ExtrasX.X disk, so if you don't have an external drive you will have to 
swap disks a couple of times.

